body:
I&#039;ve said it before and I will say it again, your own score should be what gives or takes LP so you can lose LP based on your own retardation and not what your team is trying to do.

3 out of my last 5 lost rank games have been loses due to my team throwing the game due mainly to no fucking idea how to group up and play like a team.

Last game Nasus spent some 25 minutes solo farming, mostly top, so I just said to the team to follow Nasus since he won&#039;t ever group with us and tried twice to take Baron with a full enemy team. 3 games, 3 which we were in front for most of the game were lost because my team could not group up and we would just die.

I feel like a broken record in these games.

&quot;Let&#039;s group or we will die&quot;
&quot;Let&#039;s group or we will die&quot;
&quot;Let&#039;s group or we will die&quot;

And guess what, we didn&#039;t group, and died with at least one person wandering into the ether. 2 of those loses were in my promo games, and in both games I said the same thing about halfway when we were winning &quot;Hey, I might get my promotion now&quot;... sure, that was never going to happen.

replies.body:
LP gain is based on your own MMR. 

Teammates ruining games will always be there, my last ranked we were winning with a better team comp when Ahri decides to afk cos Ezreal stole a blue buff in the enemy jungle side.

But I'm not complaining. There's always a next game you can win. {{sticker:slayer-pantheon-popcorn}}
